06/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The director of the USAID mission to Macedonia, Dick Goldman, officially opened the Centre for Sustainable Development in Bitola on Thursday (5 June). The centre will promote co-operation among local authorities, non-governmental organisations and the private sector on various multiethnic projects. It will also organise teamwork training and projects for democracy, civil society and information technology. The centre will establish a regional youth center, with activities sponsored by the German government.The Balkan Association for Friendship and Co-operation, USAID, the Institute for Sustainable Communities and the Confidence Building Initiative established the centre. (MIA-5/06/03)
